{"word":"μαντεῖος","slug":"μαντεῖος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μαντεῖος</b></el> <el>(μαντεῖος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> for <a href='S:μαντικός'><el>μαντικός</el></a>\n<p/><i>oracular, prophetic</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>μ. ἄναξ</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> Apollo, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}